 <H1>Translating ISA Hierarchies to Relations</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>General approach:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>3 relations: Employees, Hourly_Emps and Contract_Emps.
<UL>
<LI>Hourly_Emps:  Every employee is recorded in Employees.  For hourly emps, extra info recorded in Hourly_Emps (hourly_wages, hours_worked, ssn); must delete Hourly_Emps tuple if referenced Employees tuple is deleted).
<LI>Queries involving all employees easy, those involving just Hourly_Emps require a join to get some attributes.
</UL></UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Alternative:  Just Hourly_Emps and Contract_Emps.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Hourly_Emps:  ssn, name, lot, hourly_wages, hours_worked.
<LI>Each employee must be in one of these two subclasses.    </UL></UL></P>
